The International CES is all about innovation – the most important technologies in our homes were unveiled at CES, including the VCR, DVD player, HDTV, satellite radio, and much more. Why does the average U.S. household have 24 consumer electronics devices? Because CE products improve our lives, and in times like these, making life good – especially in our homes – is more important than ever. Everyone in the technology industry knows that the International CES is the hub of innovation – and the 2009 CES promises the next generation of technological innovation from 2,700 companies all in one place. <BR><BR><A href="/news/30daysInnovation.asp">Today we launch “30 Days of Innovations: The Countdown to CES,”</A> a window into the kind of technological innovation only found at CES. We’ll show you 30 new CES exhibitors – a new one each day – from among more than 300 companies that will be showing their innovations to CES attendees for the first time this year. These 30 companies we’ll showcase are just the beginning – imagine learning about the next generation of technology from 2,700 of the world’s leading companies across 30 industry segments, including electronics, content, gaming, in-vehicle and much more. <BR><BR>
<H4>
<H3>30 Days of Innovation: A Countdown to CES</H3>Day 30<BR>Chumby: Cuddly<EM> and</EM> Functional</H4><A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5667481/Chumby-Industries-Inc-/Details.aspx"><IMG height=69 hspace=8 src="/images/content/chumby_logo_text90.gif" width=239 align=left border=0></A><BR>Our first day on the Countdown to CES allows us to highlight a new CES exhibitor that shows technology can be both functional and cuddly.<BR><BR><IMG height=134 src="/images/photos/chlatte_174x162.jpg" width=172 align=right>Every once in a while, a CE product comes along with the right combination of innovation and fun that simply makes people smile, and <A href="http://www.chumby.com/" target=_blank>Chumby</A> definitely has that power. <A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5667481/Chumby-Industries-Inc-/Details.aspx">Chumby</A> takes the best of the Internet and puts it into a soft, playful and (dare&nbsp;we say) cute little package. Music, sports scores, weather, news, gaming and messaging are all among the over 1,000 different widgets that <A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5667481/Chumby-Industries-Inc-/Details.aspx">Chumby</A> makes available.<BR><BR>This squeezable Internet tool is Wi-Fi enabled and costs less than $200.&nbsp;It is the ultimate push-pull Internet device — you tell <A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5667481/Chumby-Industries-Inc-/Details.aspx">Chumby</A> what information you want, and it finds it on the Internet automatically for you and updates itself constantly. <A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5667481/Chumby-Industries-Inc-/Details.aspx">Chumby</A> can even become an Internet radio through Pandora.&nbsp;To keep itself fresh, <A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5667481/Chumby-Industries-Inc-/Details.aspx">Chumby</A> has a Linux-based, open-source platform that is open to developers who want to improve the product with cool new widgets — exactly the kind of spirit of entrepreneurship that keeps our industry humming.
